HEADWORD: Clacker
<hw>Clack"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
clacks; that which clacks; especially, the clapper of a mill.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A claqueur. See <er>Claqueur</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clad</ent>⟦br⟧
